      "kwargs": {
        "content": "I’ve completed the requested process for tour J09D:\n\n1. Created a temporary table `J09D_temp` with all rows from `decision_table` where `TOUR` starts with `\"J09D\"` and added the `ENTSCHEIDUNG` column.\n2. Classified each house (`HAUS`) based on its number of distinct equipment numbers (`EQUNR`):\n   - `< 3` EQUNR → `ENTSCHEIDUNG = 'KSA'`\n   - `≥ 3` EQUNR → `ENTSCHEIDUNG = 'EVU'`\n3. Enriched the data:\n   - Joined with `eablg` on `ANLAGE = Installation` to bring in `\"Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.\"`.\n   - Joined with `sales_master` and `net_master` on `EQUNR`.\n   - When sales data existed, used only sales fields and left the net fields unused; when sales data was missing, used net data.\n4. Exported the final result as `J09D.csv` with exactly these columns and order:\n\n   - `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`\n   - `HAUS`\n   - `ANLAGE`\n   - `ME_MA_ID`\n   - `EQUNR`\n   - `HOUSE_NUM1`\n   - `ENTSCHEIDUNG`\n   - `TITLE`\n   - `FORENAME`\n   - `SURNAME`\n   - `STREET`\n   - `STREETNO`\n   - `POST_CODE1`\n   - `CITY1`\n   - `CITY2`\n   - `EMAIL`\n\n5. Sent the CSV as an email attachment to `meter.readings@evu.com` with a short note.\n6. Dropped the temporary table `J09D_temp` from the database.\n\nIf you’d like, I can also export or re-run this for a different tour code with adjusted rules.",
